    "title": [
      "[Crawling Shore, Incline]"
    ],
    "description": [
      "Gravel-clad and jagged, an incline climbs away from the shore toward a highland ridge that overlooks the water.  Gulls and other sea birds have stained the rocks with their leavings, but otherwise the shale is unrelieved and tenebrous.  The desolate expanse of black stone is mostly impassible, but a rocky shoreline trail connects the shore with a low point in the ridgeway."
    ],
